body:
BreatheCode has a library of components hosted on this repository, and the documentation for the components is being built on storybooks and there is a [live demo here](https://breatheco-de.github.io/react-components/): 

# Document the KPI Progress Component

We need someone to finish the stories about the KPI progress component [located here](https://github.com/breatheco-de/react-components/tree/master/src/kpi-progress):

![KPI progress preview](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/breatheco-de/react-components/master/docs/img/progress_kpi.png)

## Steps to create a story for this component

1. Fork and clone the repository to your local environment.
2. Locate the component you want to build the stories to inside the `src/` folder of the project.
3. Open the component JSX and read the prop-types to understand how to interact with it.
4. Add the storybook to the `storybook/index.stories.js`
```jsx
//for example, this is a small story for the button component
storiesOf('Button', module).add('with text', () => (<Theme.Theme>
    <Button 
      label={text('Label', 'Click Me!')} 
      icon={text('Label', 'fab fa-trash')}
      type={select('Type', ['light'], 'light')}
      dropdown={[
        { label: 'First action', url: 'hello' }
      ]}
      onClick={action('checkbox-click')}
    > 
    I am a dropdown
    </Button>
</Theme.Theme>));
```
NOTE: Use [addon-knobs](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@storybook/addon-knobs) to specify the properties and [addon-actions](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@storybook/addon-actions) to simulate the events (onClick onChange, etc.)

5. Run storybooks by doing: `$ npm run storybook`
